OL,3,CPost Office campaigner Alan Bates to
OL,4,Creject 'offensive' compensation offer
OL,6,FThe government confirmed plans for
OL,7,F"full and fair compensation" to those
OL,8,Faffected by the IT scandal in 2022,
OL,9,Fwhich between 1999 and 2015 saw more
OL,10,Fthan 700 staff members wrongly
OL,11,Fprosecuted of theft, false accounting
OL,12,Fand fraud due to faulty accounting
OL,13,Fsoftware called Horizon.
OL,15,F"'Full and fair' might be His
OL,16,FMajesty's Government's interpretation,
OL,17,Fbut in reality, the offer is derisory,
OL,18,Foffensive and after all this time,
OL,19,Fyes, cruel. I will absolutely be
OL,20,Fturning this offer for financial
OL,21,Fredress down.
