OL,3,CPost Office campaigner Alan Bates to
OL,4,Creject 'offensive' compensation offer
OL,6,FA government spokesman told the
OL,7,FTelegraph: "If any applicant to the
OL,8,FGLO (Group Litigation Order) scheme
OL,9,Ffeels that they are owed more than is
OL,10,Fbeing offered, we are happy to discuss
OL,11,Fthe evidence with their legal advisers.
OL,13,F"If we can't agree, decisions will be
OL,14,Fmade by an independent panel that
OL,15,Fincludes legal and accountancy
OL,16,Fexperts, who ensure fair redress based
OL,17,Fon the evidence."
